Chief Justice nominee David Maraga will reform the judiciary and dismantle cartels , North Mugirango MP Charles Geni has said. Justice Maraga is the right man for the job because his integrity and reputation is unquestionable, he said. We are proud as a community because we have produced the second Chief Justice under the new constitutional dispensation. This has put us on the national map again, the MP added.Maraga, a Kisumu Court of Appeal judge, comes from West Mugirango, Nyamira county. But he settled in Nakuru where he had practiced as a lawyer for several years.Justice Maraga, 64, was ranked first in the JSC interviews with 84 marks.